import cfnlint
from cfnlint.decode import decode
from cfnlint.runner import Runner

# Test template containing a cloudfront distribution with a TargetOriginId error
TEST_TEMPLATE = '''
Resources:
  ReverseProxyCloudfrontDistribution:
    Type: 'AWS::CloudFront::Distribution'
    Properties:
      DistributionConfig:
        Enabled: true
        Origins:
          - Id: valid-origin-id
            DomainName: valid.domain.com
            CustomOriginConfig:
              OriginProtocolPolicy: 'https-only'
        DefaultCacheBehavior:
          TargetOriginId: invalid-origin-id  # Incorrect ID causing the error
'''

# Decode the template to handle it with cfn-lint
template, _ = decode(TEST_TEMPLATE, "test.yaml")

# Run cfn-lint runner
runner = Runner()
matches = list(runner.run(filename="test.yaml", template=template))

# Print out any matches (errors) found
for match in matches:
    print(match)
